"8WRGG08..1B1" is silkscreened on the board in the FCC photos.
An RDC version of this device may have been released. :The FCC ID for this version is KA2DI524UP (schematics) :and the device is an [[AMIT WUC1280L]]
[http://www.linux-mips.org/wiki/Realtek_SOC This device is noted on the '''linux-mips''' wiki as using RT8560B]. :It links to this (now defunct) page on [http://web.archive.org/web/20100209052343/http://ossfans.org/DI524UP '''ossfans.org''' (via archive.org)] :Specifications are noted as... :*4 MB Flash :*16 MB SDRAM :*1x USB (1.1?) :*2x Ethernet (1x WAN, 1x LAN) :*1x WLAN (RTL8185L)
